CORNELIUS NEPOS was the contemporary and friend of Cicero, Atticus, and Catullus. He was a native probably of Hostilia, now Ostiglz'a, a small town of Gallia Cispa- dana, on the Po, to the southeast of Verona, and between this latter place and Mutina, now Ilffodena. He died dui- ing the reign of Augustus. No other particulars with re- gard to his personal history have been transmitted to us. He is known, however, to have written the following pieces, all of which are now lost:

1. Chronica. An Epitome of Universal History, it would appear, in three books.
